<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa View 16 GB Video MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>A little rough on the video sync
<Date>Mon Jan 21 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>Nice unit, but not perfect with the video (yet).  The media conversion program that automatically appears on the desktop with the first sync does not recognize the sansa view.  After going to the sandisk website and updating the firmware, reformating the sansa and downloading the new media convertor from the sansa site, I now have video on my sansa view. It may not all be Sandisk's fault.  The problem requiring reformatting only occured after trying to sync to windows media player.   Actually it is my daughters, and about an hour into working with her on the above process, she asked if it was supposed to be this difficult.  Hard to answer.  She did not understand why it would not work out of the box.     Unless Sandisk has this better put together, plan on a couple of hours updating the firmware............ and explaining to your daughter why it is new and doesn't work at first.  Other than the video grief, nice unit.  
