<Review ID>1037989
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa View 16 GB Video MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>View 16gb
<Date>Sun Jan 27 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>This player supports many different file types and has a long battery life. It is designed well, and the firmware is decent. It will freeze up sometimes but will output audio while frozen. This freeze is not very common and usually goes away in less than ten seconds for the most part. For videos, I was unable to use sansa media converter (it installed fine but there was something with vista that caused a problem I think, because I am unable to access the files in such a way where it works with WMP), but windows media encoder works fine (just use CBR video). Audio quality is great, and the battery lasts a long time (not sure if it is truly 35 hrs but I wouldn't doubt it). Supports .m4a files, I don't remember if it is advertised as such though. Would recommend, the expandable memory works without a problem, there is a small icon next to the files when viewing with the media player to differentiate the location of the files.  
