<Overall>2

<Review ID>7395848
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa View 16 GB Video MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Best Value Among Flash Players
<Date>Tue Jan 29 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>In terms of features per dollar the Sandisk Sansa View is by far the most impressive offering on the market.  Though it may not be as sleek or as small as some of its more expensive competitors, it makes up for it with features and performance.  Pros: Massive amount of storage for the price. Expandability with microSD slot. Support (not listed in specs strangely enough) for non-DRM Apple AAC/A4C files; this means iTunes Plus and other DRM-free iTunes Music. Compatibility with more online stores than almost any other player. Amazing battery life when listening to music (more like 30 than 35.) Abundant features like voice recording and FM tuner.  Cons: Only 5 hours of actual battery life for video-playing. Casing feels less sturdy than some other players. Not many cases out there for it.  Bottom Line: I love this thing.  Great price, great features, good quality sound.  I strongly recommend this for anyone wanting more bang for their buck than offered by some of the more known brands.  
<Overall>5

