<Content>I got mine a couple of weeks ago and once I got the Firmware update it's been great! I also have the Sansa E280 (8Gig) and was very happy with it so I had high expectations for the view.  I really was disappointed that they still use the Windows Media Player to manage the media. I guess some people have no problems with the WMP but never seems to work correctly for me.  When I got my Sansa E280 I found a program from BakMyTunes called saCaster ($14.95 and worth twice as much!) that manages my music, lets me create and manage all the playlists I want, backs up and restores the media files and allows me to subscribe to and manage Podcasts directly.  When I got my View I contacted BakMyTunes support and found out that they already had a update available for the View and it's free to registered users!  The only negative I have for the View is that it doesn't support playlists created in the MSC mode. I hope with enough people complaining they will fix this.  For me this is Sandisk's best player yet!!!   
