<Content>Overall, I've been very pleased with my Sansa View, and do not regret buying it. For the price, it's one of the best and largest-capacity players available, and the interface is comfortable and easy to use. However, the firmware (code that the device itself runs) is a little buggy, and you really want to keep the View in a protective case (especially if you store it in a pocket with your keys).  Pros: Great capacity of flash memory for the price. Excellent battery life (30+ hours). Comfortable size (fits easily in your hand or your pocket). Works across different OSes and programs. Simple and practical interface.  Cons: Firmware bug: sometimes won't leave hold mode until restarted. Firmware bug: Occasionally takes a few moments to update song display. Casing and screen susceptible to scratching. Uses proprietary cable for data/charging (USB to SanDisk dock).  The firmware is getting periodically updated, and is already good enough in general, but glitches such as described above prevent it from having a really polished feel (and a fifth star).  While I'm no audiophile and can't really compare audio quality well, I've been happy with the sound the View produces, especially with the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000IG66VS/ref=cm_cr_asin_lnk/105-8687151-6120413">JBuds Hi-Fi Noise-Reducing Ear Buds (Black)</a> I bought to use with it.   
